so let's move it down.

00:48.764 --> 00:50.306
- Okay.
- All right.

00:50.306 --> 00:51.680
Good.
Thank you.

00:54.639 --> 00:56.389
Uh, excuse me,
Señor  Larry.

00:56.389 --> 00:59.306
All the lights in here
and in the hallway,
they're all fixed.

00:59.306 --> 01:01.473
You no have no more humming,
no more vibrating.

01:01.473 --> 01:03.722
- Everything is fixed.
- Oh! Cesar, thank you so much.

01:03.722 --> 01:05.847
That was driving me crazy,
that humming.

01:05.847 --> 01:08.056
Anything else
you need from me,
you give me a call

01:08.056 --> 01:09.972
and I'll come here
and fix it right away, okay?

01:09.972 --> 01:11.348
Oh, hey, Cesar.

01:13.680 --> 01:16.764
- That's for you.
- Oh. Oh, no, no, Señor  Larry.
I cannot accept that money.

01:16.764 --> 01:18.473
This is my job.
This is what I do.

01:18.473 --> 01:20.556
It's a little bonus
for you, a little extra.
Take it.

01:20.556 --> 01:23.639
Oh, it means--
it means a lot to me,
Mr. Larry,

01:23.639 --> 01:25.181
but I cannot take this.

01:25.181 --> 01:27.056
I-- I just don't
feel comfortable.

01:27.056 --> 01:29.264
- This is what I do, sir.
- ( scoffs )

01:29.264 --> 01:32.972
Oh, Cesar, this is--
this is unprecedented!

01:32.972 --> 01:36.181
This is rarer than
a man turning down sex,
what you've just done.

01:36.181 --> 01:37.722
It just--
it doesn't happen!

01:37.722 --> 01:39.889
( chuckles )
Okay, Señor  Larry.

01:39.889 --> 01:41.722
I've never turned down
sex in my life.

01:41.722 --> 01:43.431
( chuckles )
Me neither.

01:43.431 --> 01:47.222
Huh! Cesar, this will not
be forgotten anytime soon.

01:47.222 --> 01:49.598
- Have a nice day.
- Very commendable.

01:51.306 --> 01:53.097
Larry:
So now, for some reason,

01:53.097 --> 01:55.556
Funkhouser's gotten back
together with this woman.

01:55.556 --> 01:57.722
- I don't know why.
She hates my guts.
- Aww.

01:57.722 --> 01:59.889
But nevertheless,
he wants to go to brunch

01:59.889 --> 02:03.514
and see if we can
all get along, you know,
so it's gonna be very awkward.

02:03.514 --> 02:05.097
Just because
of the tap water?

02:05.097 --> 02:07.930
- Tap water, yes.
Tap water.
- Wow.

02:07.930 --> 02:09.722
Hey, Eddie, breakfast!

02:09.722 --> 02:10.722
( whispers )
Wow, tap water.

02:10.722 --> 02:11.764
Here you go,
sweetie.

02:11.764 --> 02:13.014
Wow, look at
the young man today!

02:13.014 --> 02:14.722
Very nice hoodie
you got there.

02:14.722 --> 02:16.556
Mom, you're still
dating this guy?

02:16.556 --> 02:19.181
- Yes, honey--
- Yes, and she's
enjoying it very much.

02:19.181 --> 02:21.097
- Take your toast.
- Where's the butter?

02:21.097 --> 02:23.514
It's right there,
quite visible.

02:23.514 --> 02:26.222
I can't see the butter.
Do it again.

02:26.222 --> 02:28.473
( sighs )
He needs to see
the butter.

02:28.473 --> 02:30.930
- I'll eat this one
and I'll make you another one.
- ( sighs )

02:32.680 --> 02:35.680
- Are you two having sex?
- That's Mommy's business.

02:35.680 --> 02:37.972
It's not really your business,
but to tell you the truth,

02:37.972 --> 02:40.264
it's imminent, okay?

02:40.264 --> 02:41.556
Gross.

02:43.639 --> 02:46.014
( sighs )
Sorry, he's really been
having a tough time lately.

02:46.014 --> 02:48.097
I-- I don't know
how you let him get away
with that toast thing.

02:48.097 --> 02:50.722
This kid needs
some structure in his life.
He needs some discipline!

02:50.722 --> 02:52.514
- I know, I know.
- You're not tough enough.

02:52.514 --> 02:55.181
I-- I know.
There's this
private school, and, uh...

02:55.181 --> 02:59.097
I've been thinking about
sending him, but it's really
tough to get into, and...

02:59.097 --> 03:00.556
I wanted to ask you
a question.

03:00.556 --> 03:02.847
Please say no if this
is at all inappropriate,

03:02.847 --> 03:06.181
but Susie happened to mention
this very same school,
Pemberton Academy,

03:06.181 --> 03:07.639
where I'm trying
to get him in.

03:07.639 --> 03:09.639
You had donated
some "Seinfeld" stuff there.

03:09.639 --> 03:12.181
My assistant
takes care of all that.
I just, you know.

03:12.181 --> 03:15.514
- Okay, I just didn't know
if you knew somebody, or...
- Nah, I really don't.

03:15.514 --> 03:18.097
- That's fine, that's fine.
- If I could help, I would,
but I don't know.

03:18.097 --> 03:21.014
You know, I feel
weird about sending him
to boarding school anyway.

03:23.056 --> 03:25.097
- Boarding school?
- Yeah.

03:25.097 --> 03:28.556
- How far away is it?
- It's about an hour
and a half.

03:28.556 --> 03:31.514
I actually think
it would be the best for him,
but it would be hard for me

03:31.514 --> 03:33.306
- just to be rattling around--
- I completely agree with you.

03:33.306 --> 03:35.139
I think it would be
a fantastic thing for him.

03:35.139 --> 03:37.764
- Do you, really?
- It's gotta be the--
you know what?

03:37.764 --> 03:40.805
Get me a name,
get me a number--
whatever I can do to help.

03:40.805 --> 03:41.889
- No.
- Yes!

03:41.889 --> 03:43.889
Give me some information,
done!

03:43.889 --> 03:46.014
That's really nice
of you, Larry.

03:46.014 --> 03:48.598
Thank you so much.
It's gonna be so good for him.

03:48.598 --> 03:53.722
Look, if I can send him
an hour and a half away,
I'm... more than happy to.

03:56.514 --> 03:58.639
- Larry: If I got
those glasses...
- Bridget: Yeah?

03:58.639 --> 04:00.514
We'd be--
we'd be twins.

04:00.514 --> 04:02.556
That would be
kind of hideous,
wouldn't it?

04:02.556 --> 04:05.014
Have you ever seen a couple
with the same glasses?

04:05.014 --> 04:07.431
By the way, when I say couple,
I'm not referring to us
as a couple.

04:07.431 --> 04:10.348
- Yeah, excuse me.
What are you-- hold on.
- No, no, I'm not going there.

04:10.348 --> 04:13.514
We're-- I--
you have not bought me
the same glasses.

04:13.514 --> 04:16.847
We don't have it
like that just yet,
my friend.

04:16.847 --> 04:18.056
- Hi, guys.
- Hi.

04:18.056 --> 04:19.181
Can I bring you some water
while you wait?

04:19.181 --> 04:20.805
Still or sparkling?

04:20.805 --> 04:23.014
- Sparkling. Yeah.
- Yeah, sparkling.

04:23.014 --> 04:25.514
Ugh, boy,
I can't tell you,
I'm so relieved.

04:25.514 --> 04:28.473
Thanks again
for helping me out with
the boarding school thing.

04:28.473 --> 04:30.930
So, before I call
the, um...

04:30.930 --> 04:33.389
- Pemberton.
- Pemberton, yes.
Pemberton.

04:33.389 --> 04:37.722
Do they-- do they know
about the, uh, Asperger's?

04:37.722 --> 04:39.930
Oh, yeah, mm-hmm.
Yeah, they're a great school.

04:39.930 --> 04:44.514
They're-- they can--
they're just equipped to handle
all kinds of special kids.

04:44.514 --> 04:47.056
Mm-hmm.
Mm-hmm.

04:47.056 --> 04:50.473
Has he been diagnosed
by a doctor, or is this
your opinion?

04:50.473 --> 04:54.805
He's on the spectrum.
( chuckles ) Yeah.

04:54.805 --> 04:56.598
How do you know?

04:56.598 --> 05:00.389
You can see in his behavior
and what people have said,
and, you know--

05:00.389 --> 05:02.056
he's, you know--

05:02.056 --> 05:05.847
he's been diagnosed
on the-- on the spectrum.

05:08.930 --> 05:10.056
Okay.

05:10.056 --> 05:11.972
- ( phone ringing )
- Oh.

05:14.222 --> 05:16.181
- Hello?
- Cesar: Señor Larry,

05:16.181 --> 05:18.014
it's Cesar
from the office.

05:18.014 --> 05:19.431
- Who?
- Cesar!

05:19.431 --> 05:21.805
You gave me the tip
and I didn't take it?

05:21.805 --> 05:23.680
Yeah?

05:23.680 --> 05:26.181
I'm here
at the office building,
fixing a leak,

05:26.181 --> 05:28.264
and I was just wondering,
after I'm done,

05:28.264 --> 05:31.764
I could go to your office
and watch the Argentina
and Mexico game.

05:31.764 --> 05:35.014
It's a very important game.
It's for-- to qualify
in the World Cup.

05:35.014 --> 05:37.847
Why-- why--
why do you have to go--
why my office?

05:37.847 --> 05:40.639
Because you got
all the channels, sir.

05:40.639 --> 05:43.972
- Yeah... yeah, okay.
- Gracias, Señor Larry!

05:43.972 --> 05:47.097
I will not forget this.
You are the man.

05:47.097 --> 05:49.014
- Okay.
- Who's that?

05:49.014 --> 05:52.639
- This handyman
in my office building...
- Uh-huh.

05:52.639 --> 05:55.847
...wants to go into my office
to watch a soccer game.

05:55.847 --> 05:57.764
I offered him a tip,
but he didn't take the tip,

05:57.764 --> 06:01.348
so I feel like
I'm a little obligated
to let him watch the game.

06:01.348 --> 06:02.431
It's tricky.

06:02.431 --> 06:04.264
- Hello!
- Oh, hey!

06:04.264 --> 06:05.473
Sorry we're late.

06:05.473 --> 06:06.514
- Hi, I'm Marilyn.
- LD.

06:06.514 --> 06:07.930
- Hi!
- Hi, nice to meet you.

06:07.930 --> 06:09.847
- Yes, hi.
- Hi. Marty Funkhouser.

06:09.847 --> 06:11.639
- Hi, great to meet you.
- Great to meet you!

06:11.639 --> 06:14.514
So, I-- I just wanna say,
before we begin,

06:14.514 --> 06:18.805
I-- I'd like to apologize
for what happened between us.

06:18.805 --> 06:22.181
That is not
a true representation
of who I am.

06:22.181 --> 06:24.097
- Let's start fresh.
- That means a lot to me.
Okay.

06:24.097 --> 06:26.139
- Yes! Yes!
- Yes, let's do it.

06:26.139 --> 06:28.972
Some sparkling water
for the table?

06:28.972 --> 06:32.764
No, no. We-- no,
we don't want that.
We want some tap water.

06:32.764 --> 06:35.014
- You don't want sparkling?
- No, get that out of here.
Tap.

06:35.014 --> 06:36.972
- Well, it's unfiltered.
- Better.

06:36.972 --> 06:38.598
Water is water.
We're not water snobs.

06:38.598 --> 06:40.014
- Server: Very good.
- Larry: We don't care.

06:40.014 --> 06:41.389
While you bring the tap,

06:41.389 --> 06:43.222
bring us the best
bottle of champagne

06:43.222 --> 06:44.847
you have in the house
to drink.

06:44.847 --> 06:46.431
- ( all cheering )
- Okay?

06:46.431 --> 06:47.847
We're gonna live it up!

06:47.847 --> 06:50.722
- ( chuckles )
- Yeah, you know, sure.

06:50.722 --> 06:52.847
Thank you, Larry.
I really appreciate
your apology.

06:52.847 --> 06:54.847
- Larry: Oh, yes.
- No, it means a lot to me.

06:54.847 --> 06:56.264
And some tap water
for the table.

06:56.264 --> 06:57.930
Tap water for the table.
Look at this.

06:57.930 --> 07:00.389
Look at this
beautiful tap water.
We got some here...

07:05.556 --> 07:07.431
- Ah, look at that.
- Mmm.

07:07.431 --> 07:08.930
Ah, it really looks good.

07:08.930 --> 07:11.889
( people chattering )

07:11.889 --> 07:13.598
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
- Oh, come on, buddy.

07:13.598 --> 07:15.097
- There's a line.
- There's a line.

07:15.097 --> 07:16.264
You can't
just walk up here.

07:16.264 --> 07:18.139
Come on, man,
you're being rude.

07:18.139 --> 07:20.722
- They're in line.
- Man: You gotta get
to the back, buddy.

07:20.722 --> 07:23.722
- I'm just
getting some potatoes.
- Woman: I don't care.

07:23.722 --> 07:25.348
One-- one minute!

07:25.348 --> 07:28.431
One minute!
Just a minute!

07:28.431 --> 07:29.764
Are you getting seconds?

07:29.764 --> 07:31.389
Yes, sir.

07:31.389 --> 07:33.056
The man
is getting seconds.

07:33.056 --> 07:35.014
- It doesn't matter.
- But that's not a rule.

07:35.014 --> 07:38.139
The man has already
waited on this line.

07:38.139 --> 07:41.222
- Larry, we're hungry.
- Larry: We're all hungry.

07:41.222 --> 07:42.389
I'm hungry, too!

07:42.389 --> 07:43.847
But to make him wait

07:43.847 --> 07:47.639
another 10 minutes
for a few measly potatoes?

07:47.639 --> 07:49.930
- Shame on you!
Shame on all of you!
- Okay.

07:49.930 --> 07:52.431
That's not how we do things
here in America.

07:52.431 --> 07:56.473
We don't wait for seconds!
Never, never wait for seconds!

07:56.473 --> 07:58.930
- ( whispering )
- It's fine, it's good.
It's fine.

07:58.930 --> 08:02.264
Sir, I would be proud
to serve you.

08:02.264 --> 08:04.473
- What do you want?
- Potatoes.

08:06.556 --> 08:09.056
- Thank you.
Thank you, sir.
- Woman: Sure, sure.

08:09.056 --> 08:11.680
You're welcome.

08:11.680 --> 08:14.764
- It's okay, really.
- I didn't mean to overreact
like that.

08:14.764 --> 08:16.930
- Woman: Enjoy.
- Woman #2: Enjoy yourself.

08:16.930 --> 08:18.431
Thank you.
Thanks.

08:19.598 --> 08:20.889
- ( cork pops )
- Larry: Ah!

08:20.889 --> 08:22.389
- Oh, I love that sound!
- All right!

08:22.389 --> 08:26.097
- You like that?
- I love that sound!

08:26.097 --> 08:29.014
I mean, the good thing here
is that if we want seconds,

08:29.014 --> 08:30.764
- we go right to the front.
- Bridget: Straight to
the front.

08:30.764 --> 08:32.097
- Right?
- Yep.

08:34.222 --> 08:38.556
Boy, oh, boy.
Ha, that's a lot
of ketchup there.

08:38.556 --> 08:40.306
I like ketchup.

08:40.306 --> 08:43.514
Yeah, uh, it seems
a little excessive, no?

08:43.514 --> 08:45.306
- Here we go!
- Living it up!

08:45.306 --> 08:48.389
- Happiness,
living it up! Okay?
- Bridget: Cheers!

08:48.389 --> 08:50.389
I mean, you use
too much ketchup,
you know what happens?

08:50.389 --> 08:52.889
They-- they convert to packs,
to the little packets.

08:52.889 --> 08:55.639
Is there a ketchup shortage?
Like, "Oh, we're gonna
run out of ketchup."

08:55.639 --> 08:57.639
I wasn't saying
there's a ketchup shortage,

08:57.639 --> 09:00.722
it's just that
if everybody uses
as much ketchup as you do,

09:00.722 --> 09:02.056
they would stop buying it.

09:02.056 --> 09:04.473
As a matter of fact,
I think I need more ketchup.

09:04.473 --> 09:05.306
Mmm.

09:07.181 --> 09:09.014
- Bridget: Wow.
- Hmm!

09:09.014 --> 09:10.805
Funkhouser:
Why are we talking
about this?

09:10.805 --> 09:13.473
There's no way she could
finish all that ketchup.
Is there?

09:13.473 --> 09:14.972
Watch me!

09:16.805 --> 09:19.181
Funkhouser:
Let's just change
the subject, okay?

09:19.181 --> 09:20.514
Potatoes are delicious.

09:20.514 --> 09:21.847
- Huh.
- Larry: Yeah.

09:21.847 --> 09:25.181
- Marilyn:
Oh, my God! Oh!
- ( gasps )

09:25.181 --> 09:27.139
- Oh, my God!
- Funkhouser: Don't do that,
don't do that.

09:27.139 --> 09:28.680
Can we get
a wet towel, somebody?

09:28.680 --> 09:30.306
That's okay.
It's okay, it's okay.

09:30.306 --> 09:32.348
It's okay.
Yeah, your sweater
covers it fine.

09:32.348 --> 09:34.847
You know,
I-- I think I want--
I want to go home.

09:34.847 --> 09:36.222
Oh, no!

09:36.222 --> 09:38.056
- It's just
a really bad stain.
- Yeah, go.

09:38.056 --> 09:39.764
- No, Larry,
it's not that bad.
- You got a bad stain.

09:39.764 --> 09:40.930
I'm gonna go home.

09:40.930 --> 09:42.431
I'm just feeling
very uncomfortable.

09:42.431 --> 09:44.348
- Oh, I'm so sorry.
- Yeah, go.

09:44.348 --> 09:46.014
It's a--
it's a really bad stain.

09:46.014 --> 09:48.514
It's a "go home" stain,
you know what I mean?

09:48.514 --> 09:50.348
- It was the fork.
- I think it was the ketchup.

09:50.348 --> 09:52.680
- Let's not argue over this.
- Marilyn: I'm so sorry.

09:52.680 --> 09:55.514
It was lovely to meet you.
You seem lovely.

09:55.514 --> 09:57.598
- Yeah, take her home.
- It's such a shame.

09:57.598 --> 09:59.639
Nice job, once again.

09:59.639 --> 10:02.473
- One of those things.
- Gosh, another time, I guess.

10:02.473 --> 10:04.056
- Bye.
- Bye.

10:04.056 --> 10:06.431
Wow, I feel so bad.

10:06.431 --> 10:08.181
That was
a disgusting display.

10:08.181 --> 10:09.639
You couldn't let
the ketchup go.

10:09.639 --> 10:11.764
- Couldn't let it go.
- Oh, boy.

10:11.764 --> 10:14.639
Guess what.

10:14.639 --> 10:16.972
Who's paying
for the expensive champagne?

10:16.972 --> 10:18.889
- Oh.
- Yeah.

10:24.264 --> 10:27.222
- ( door opens )
- ( footsteps approaching )

10:29.514 --> 10:31.389
I want to thank you

10:31.389 --> 10:34.056
for defending me
in front of the mob.

10:34.056 --> 10:37.056
Oh, oh.
Yes, of course.

10:37.056 --> 10:40.222
That was, uh, terrible.
You had already waited.

10:40.222 --> 10:42.014
What was the point
of going back again?

10:42.014 --> 10:43.930
You would've lost
your appetite.

10:43.930 --> 10:45.930
I agree with you,
Mr. David.

10:48.972 --> 10:50.264
How do you know my name?

10:51.805 --> 10:54.598
I know everything
about you.

10:54.598 --> 10:56.680
I was sitting there
having my brunch,

10:56.680 --> 10:59.431
and I saw you.

10:59.431 --> 11:03.139
And I was thinking,
as a devout Muslim,

11:03.139 --> 11:05.389
I should kill this man.

11:05.389 --> 11:06.722
Fatwa.

11:06.722 --> 11:09.056
And then you defended me.

11:09.056 --> 11:11.431
I thought to myself...

11:13.348 --> 11:15.764
I cannot kill this man.

11:15.764 --> 11:17.889
This man doesn't
deserve to die.

11:17.889 --> 11:20.722
No. No, I don't.
I don't!

11:20.722 --> 11:24.639
I do have some friends
in high positions.

11:24.639 --> 11:27.722
I think I need to bring
to their attention

11:27.722 --> 11:31.097
that you are not the man
they think you are.

11:31.097 --> 11:33.598
Anything you want to know,
I'll give you full access.

11:33.598 --> 11:35.222
I'm an open book.

11:35.222 --> 11:37.014
You will be hearing
from me.

11:37.014 --> 11:39.264
What-- what is your name?

11:39.264 --> 11:43.473
My name
is not important.

11:45.139 --> 11:48.389
- Hey!
- Oh, hey. Um...

11:48.389 --> 11:51.473
- You okay?
- Yeah, I was just
talking to this guy.

11:51.473 --> 11:53.639
( chuckles )
What guy?

11:53.639 --> 11:55.014
Oh.

11:55.014 --> 11:57.473
( chuckles )
Let's go.

11:57.473 --> 11:58.473
Huh.

12:01.639 --> 12:03.348
Larry:
That was a lot of fun.

12:03.348 --> 12:04.930
That horse,
he was so close!

12:04.930 --> 12:06.805
- He should've won!
- I know, I know, I know.

12:06.805 --> 12:09.056
I know.
I was-- I was
excited for you.

12:09.056 --> 12:12.764
By the way,
this is-- what are we on?
10 hours now together?

